   More than 4,000 workers at a coal mine in the southern city of Jastrzebie went on strike today 08/16/1988 to demand legalization of Solidarity and higher wages.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The miners are demanding the legalization of Solidarity and reinstatement of workers fired for union activities.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The workers are also calling for higher wages and better working conditions.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Manifest Lipcowy is the second mine in the industrial region of Silesia to experience unrest.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
